<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
    DRAFT — pending fetcher phase. Wishlist item 51c; methodology row
    "Paper-4 Phase-A capture spec — slot-resolution xStock AMM panel —
    2026-05-01 (locked)" in scryer/methodology_log.md.

    Do not `launchctl load` until `scry solana clmm-pool-state watch`
    ships (new crate `scryer-fetch-solana-pool-state`) and the schema
    `clmm_pool_state.v1` (docs/schemas.md, line 734) has its
    first-data-shipped phase row.

    Forward-only by design: replay from the swap tape would be O(swaps)
    per pool, dominantly more expensive than account-subscription
    forward-capture.

    Push-based daemon — KeepAlive, NOT StartInterval. The 60s
    `getMultipleAccounts` polled fallback path is internal to the
    fetcher, not driven by launchd.

    Geyser provider choice (Helius vs Triton vs Yellowstone vs
    operator-run node) is NOT locked in the methodology row — lands in
    the per-fetcher methodology row when the crate ships, per scryer
    hard rule #5. The plist passes `--proxy-url` to the local
    scryer-proxy by default; the daemon negotiates Geyser upstream
    through proxy config.

    Pool allowlist computed at startup from a top-K-by-TVL Whirlpool +
    Raydium-CLMM scan filtered by the 8 xStock mints; refreshed on
    daemon restart. The `--pools auto` argument is the documented
    sentinel for that on-startup scan; an explicit file can be supplied
    with `--pools /path/to/allowlist.json` if the operator wants to pin
    the set across restarts.

    Programs:
      Orca Whirlpools  whirLbMiicVdio4qvUfM5KAg6Ct8VwpYzGff3uctyCc
      Raydium CLMM     CAMMCzo5YL8w4VFF8KVHrK22GGUsp5VTaW7grrKgrWqK
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>Label</key>
    <string>com.adamnoonan.scryer.clmm-pool-state-watch</string>

    <key>ProgramArguments</key>
    <array>
        <string>/Users/adamnoonan/Library/Application Support/scryer/bin/scry</string>
        <string>solana</string>
        <string>clmm-pool-state</string>
        <string>watch</string>
        <string>--pools</string>
        <string>auto</string>
        <string>--proxy-url</string>
        <string>http://127.0.0.1:8899/rpc</string>
        <string>--source</string>
        <string>solana:clmm-pool-state:launchd</string>
        <string>--dataset</string>
        <string>/Users/adamnoonan/Library/Application Support/scryer/dataset</string>
    </array>

    <key>WorkingDirectory</key>
    <string>/Users/adamnoonan/Library/Application Support/scryer</string>

    <key>RunAtLoad</key>
    <true/>

    <key>KeepAlive</key>
    <true/>

    <key>ThrottleInterval</key>
    <integer>30</integer>

    <key>StandardOutPath</key>
    <string>/Users/adamnoonan/Library/Logs/scryer/clmm-pool-state-watch.out.log</string>
    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
    <string>/Users/adamnoonan/Library/Logs/scryer/clmm-pool-state-watch.err.log</string>

    <key>EnvironmentVariables</key>
    <dict>
        <key>SCRY_LOG</key>
        <string>info</string>
    </dict>

    <key>ProcessType</key>
    <string>Background</string>

    <key>LowPriorityIO</key>
    <true/>

    <key>Nice</key>
    <integer>5</integer>
</dict>
</plist>
